    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray with a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until the chips are golden and starting to crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/homemade-veggie-burger-and-sun-dried-tomato-mayo/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and roughly chop your<strong> red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>basil</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p><p>Drain your <strong>sweetcorn</strong> and pat the kernels completely dry with <strong>kitchen paper</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/homemade-veggie-burger-and-sun-dried-tomato-mayo/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> dried sweetcorn</strong>, <strong>chopped red onion</strong>,<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and<strong> chopped basil</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> with your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>ground cumin</strong>,<strong> tahini</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Pulse for 2-3 secs or until the mixture is roughly chopped</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/homemade-veggie-burger-and-sun-dried-tomato-mayo/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> and pulse for 2-3 secs further or until the mixture comes together to form a dough-like consistency</p><p>Shape the mixture into 1 flat <strong>burger patty </strong>per person</p><p>Tip: Add a little more<strong> </strong>flour if your mixture is too wet to handle</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/homemade-veggie-burger-and-sun-dried-tomato-mayo/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once the pan is hot, add the <strong>burger patty[ies]</strong> and cook for 2-3 min on each side or until golden then add to a baking tray (or two!), save the pan for later</p><p>Put the tray into the oven for 10 min or until golden</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/homemade-veggie-burger-and-sun-dried-tomato-mayo/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the patties are in the oven, slice your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong> into thin slices</p><p>Once golden, top each <strong>burger patty</strong> with the <strong>sliced cheese</strong>, then return the tray[s] to the oven for 3-4 min further or until the cheese is melted and the burgers are cooked through, these are your <strong>cheesy burger patty[ies]</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/homemade-veggie-burger-and-sun-dried-tomato-mayo/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wipe the reserved pan clean and return it to a medium-high heat</p><p>Slice your brioche bun[s] in half (if required!), once hot, add your<strong> brioche bun[s]</strong>, cut-side down, and cook for 3 min or until toasted and charred, then set aside until serving</p><p>Add your <strong>mayo</strong> and <strong>balsamic sun-dried tomato paste</strong> to a bowl and give it a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> sun-dried tomato mayo</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat it dry with<strong> kitchen paper</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/homemade-veggie-burger-and-sun-dried-tomato-mayo/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Assemble your burgers with a little<strong> sun-dried tomato mayo</strong>, the <strong>salad </strong>and the<strong> cheesy burger patty[ies]</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> chips</strong> and any <strong>remaining sun-dried tomato mayo</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
